scene_description_enriched: A figure, likely a woman, is depicted holding a sword upright in front of her. She wears a headdress and ornate clothing. To her left, a banner with text is visible. Above her, a decorative architectural element, possibly part of a larger structure, is suggested. The scene is rendered in a woodcut style, typical of early printed books.
scene_interpretation: This image likely represents a figure from the Old Testament or a saint, possibly Judith, known for her bravery and the sword she used to defeat Holofernes. The text on the banner may provide further context or identification.
